values:
Once when I was a wee lass
I skimmed the tops of cherry trees,
over and under and inbetween.
I circled the block on a summer breeze
and tried to recall the Seven Seas,
over and under and inbetween.
But their water rose up to the sun
spilling and running over every one!
Without much ado,
I went and grabbed my trusty spoon.
One spoon, two spoon, three spoon, FOUR.
Five spoon, six spoon, and a hundred more!
Soon the earth did reappear
and everyone thought they were in the clear.
But the earth had taken on a new shape,
after the horrifying water rape.
Cuts and bruises lined the beaches
draining its blood like millions of leeches.
But oh what a sight to behold,
before everything turned ice cold.

<c>My bracelet finally fell off today.<c/>




I transformed it into a bookmark, so I'm only a bit heartbroken.

My face hurts.
I hate wisdoom teeth.
And I hate my fat face.
But I do enjoy the pain pills. mmhmm.


Anyway, all I know is that whenever I awoke from one of my drug induced naps
my brother was the only person at my side. He came home early on a Friday
night to retrieve ice packs, or medicine, or the remote for me. The kid 
seriously amazes me sometimes. 
Someone raised him right...



Have a wonderful three day weekend everyone :)

Summer is slowly slipping away through my fingers. 
And as tragic as that is, I believe I ended it in the best possible way:
with some sourpatch kids, cucumbers, and a champagne bottle.
Makes sense.

Also, today I moved into a dorm. The whole concept of dorm life is strange.
I feel like Im at camp. I dont like bunk beds much, but I do like my roommate so 
I think Ill survive.

Come visit me at my new abode. All six of you. Do it.
We can sit on my bunk bed and draw pictures on my dry erase board!
Yeah thats right, we know how to party.

I miss my dogs. Thats pretty much it.
Pretty much.

I really love summer. It makes me... Just like a postcard Saw a bridge Saw a shipwreck Saw a sunset Discovered a tee-pee! Discovered my super strength Ran, ran, ran around Look what I found! I love it. I saw you kissing tiny flowers... Going home...

I never take it as a good sign
when death greets me on my doorstep
First thing in the morning
Or when fortunes tumble from my hair
be aware, be aware, be aware
Or when the conversations escape their confines
They travel from my lips
to your ears in perpetually parallel lines
I watch them on their march, so triumphant and proud
to have breathed life 
and been heard outloud.



So I'm going on a trip now.
I'll probably be back though.
But I'll miss you when I'm gone.
So long!!!!

So I graduated. '05 bitches... I like how there's a camera too. I thought that to be very appropriate. Look at mr. engelmann's face and travis' hat! mr. fred astaire... aww theyre so in love... aww theyre so in love too... these masks are sort of frightening... k bye.

Goodbyes are something I've grown accustomed to.
Yes, I've had some practice.
But I do have a table in my car,
with scribbled memories and people made from stars.
At least there's that.
It's become apparent that the good ones never stay in one place
too long.
I don't sleep much anymore.
I haven't seen my bed for the past three nights,
mostly because of the mounds of miscellaneous crap all over it.
I know it's still there though.
So at least there's that.

Thanks friends. 
You're all pretty amazing.

Also, double, triple, quadruple thanks to 
everyone that went to the fashion show.
That meant a lot too. 

Eighteen is looking good.

So I've decided that hitchhiking home at 5am is always a good idea.
You will either be picked up by a) a serial killer rapist or b) a hippie stoner guy.
I got choice b). It was Easter morning so I think I lucked out because of Jesus or maybe
all the serial killers are off for the holidays. Anyway, now we're friends.
I didn't get to sleep either because it was Easter and you have to wake up early to partake
in all the festivities. Sleep is a rare commodity these days. 
Awake is the new Sleep. Chins are the new Nose. Drunk is the new Sober and Straight is the new Gay.
I love it.
But really though, I hate sleep. I never have any interesting dreams. Kind of like the dead in Ring Two.
We never dream, therefore I must be dead right? Guess so. 
Who will save our souls? Hmm who? I like Jewel. She was my favorite back in the day. 
I even named my dog Jewel, but this was 6th grade okay! Now I tell people my dog's name is Jules
to sound like Pulp Fiction or something ubercool like that. But really no, it's Jewel.
I named her that in 6th grade because 6th graders do crazy, weird stuff like that.
I miss 6th grade. It was a good year for me.
I played saxophone.
I bet Jewel would be flattered to know that some crazy, weird 6th grader named her highly nervous, slightly stupid dog after her. I think Jewel appreciates crazy, weird stuff like that.
She used to live in a van and I bet she even picked up a few hitchhikers in her day.
I bet, I bet.

When things are such a mess that you don't even know where to start,
it consumes you, becomes you, is you!
You're such a goddamn mess these days,
and baby I hate to tell you this but there's no one that's going to want to clean you up.
In a constant state of inertia, your body's moving forward,
it's your head that's stuck way back there!
When everyone else is keeping in step with the spin of this earth
but I know you're dizzy and you don't want to try and keep up anymore.
Well honey, the world won't stop spinning just so you can catch your breath!
And it will keep spinning long after the last whisper escapes your lips. 
So don't take this too seriously, kid! Try to laugh,
try to smile.
So when it's the last act you'll know that it
's been a good show, as good as it could be anyway.
Atleast you passed the time. You did it.
Really, you did. 
You did you did you did you did
you did you did you did you did you did you did you did
you did you did you?

I got some shampoo in my eye and it stung real bad,

that's when I realized: I tend to be a bit of a liar.

So here's a funny story:

Today my mom was picking up the rest of the toilet paper in our yard from the infamous TPing incident and she looks into one of our bushes and finds a bag of pot. Hmmm weird? She ran in the house yelling at me and my brother and whatnot. Then she says that she is going to talk my dad into sending us to rehab. ahahhahahaha. I seriously laughed for an hour because she was so serious. 

Mom: I cant believe this!! Drugs are not good! I'm sending you to rehab!
Me: Mom, are you kidding me?
Mom: No, Im not kidding you! Im talking to your dad tonight.
Bro: Okay mom, we're going to rehab.
Mom: Ahhhblahblhablhablah!! I dont do drugs!
Me: Maybe you should.

Somtimes I wake up and find myself in a parallel universe where everything is different. But it's always the same. It's the damndest thing. To be faced with this dream-reality where the stars blend into the black sea and everyone drowns in pairs of three. To sense the coming of the dawn going in reverse. Leafing through your pages in a fashion thought perverse. You've got the charm of the defeated, checked your coat at the door and retreated. Into the reality-dream. Tearing at every seam. It's the damndest thing. To be faced with this wall, the motor's running but you stall. Like no key in the ignition, you're stuck in one position and it's hell. Where everything is different. But it's always the same. Because catch and release is the game. And baby, I know you're dying to be caught. Just to be thrown back out to sea where everyone drowns in pairs of three. I'm going to make a children's book someday.

ASU almost ruined my life today.
I'm glad it changed its mind at the last minute though.
I'll thank Mr. E on that one for finding out through his sweet connections.
Sa-weet.

Sometimes I get frustrated with Ms. Frizz because sometimes she gives me a C on
my report card which she knows is a god damn filthy lie.  
Other times she makes me write 10 page papers, which believe it or not are not interesting in the least.
And other times where she calls and wakes me up from my naps. It all just builds upon my frustration.
But today she bought me a burrito, and I remembered that she buys me lunch every other Wednesday.
So really a person that buys you lunch every other week can't be all that bad.

I also think that Peyton and Jake are the cutest couple on One Tree Hill.
I love how trivial my life is!
Sa-weet.

I pretty much received the nicest compliment ever given to me today.
I don't know.
It's just nice having someone else believe in you enough to say it out loud.

She was a wild one, she was. She floated from place to place. Wherever the wind blew her, she followed its drift. But you can't just float along on each warm front that blows through a town without gaining some kind of reputation. So a reputation she did gain. It followed her in her tracks and soon even preceded her presence. Curse the wind, that seductress! For she claimed you as her own, a slave to her every whim! And you cannot fight the nature that lives within you. How tragic to be condemned for that very same reason. But that's how things go when you decide to go where the wind blows. I apologize, Miss, because no one values a well traveled gal, so you might as well ride this one out. See where the wind will take you this time around and just know that your blessing is you'll never be in one place too long.

Alcoholism is truly appealing. Honestly, I hope to be checking myself into a Betty Ford type clinic by the age of twenty-four. Not to 'recover' or 'get well', oh no. No mostly so I can try to persuade other recovering alcoholics to go and get a drink with me when we get out to celebrate our sobriety. Tempt! Tempt! Tempt! them into submission! 
"No, it's not starting from square one again! It's a reward for making it so far! Everyone deserves a reward, dammit! Come on, here's to sobriety!" *clink*
And swallow the sweet nectar along with your hopes of climbing out of this stupor. Ah, but this stupor is so god damn good...and you know it's true. You've felt it too. So drink up, darlings. This one is on me.

No, masochism isnt the word.
It doesnt hurt, it just passes the time.
The time between the in-betweens. Yes, the in-betweens.
Those moments between sanity and utter lunacy. Those split seconds,
with a flash its gone, but its presence no less intense.
Those slow motion instants, where ambivalence fills you to the brim.
Do you stop at this red light with the traffic flowing steadily in front of you.
What if you didnt.
What if you cruised across that stop line, ignored the warning signs,
and defied the well defined.
Would that give you your thrills and make you feel alive.
Would that satisfy you and lift you out of the mundane.
Does the threat of impending death make you want to live, 
or do those lines run and bleed together so as to make it impossible to differentiate between the two.
Yes, those in-betweens.
Although, it is not harmful if you cant feel it.
Its not a struggle if youre not trying.
And its not a battle if you dont care to fight.
Its not anything really.
Its just being caught in this whirlpool, walking this tightrope, and balancing this act.
Its all just borderline.
Borderline between what and what?!
Its blurred, so if its just halfway something, we will disregard it as nothing.
And if youre an in-between...well dont be.

I love being woken up by pillows thrashing against my head. My dear brother.
I love the smell of my dear mother baking breakfast in the kitchen, follwed shortly by the piercing sound of the smoke detector. Ahhh Christmas morning. There is truly nothing like it.

I have presents that need delivering. Letters that need writing. Phone calls that need calling. Food that needs eating. DVDs that need viewing. Drinks that need drinking. So on and so forth. 

You get the idea. 

Christmas is busy.

How come it doesn't feel like it's almost Christmas?

Oh maybe it was because I just worked 9 hours straight! Yeeeah retail is my life!
We closed at 7 and I rang up my last customer a little after 730 and my manager 
came up to me and shot himself in the face, while I proceeded to collapse to the ground.
He laughed at me and left me there to rot in the middle of the fragrance aisle. Tragic.

On top of that Santa decided to be funny this year and give me something TOTALLY AWESOME, a 
little something called pink eye. hahaha, oh santa you're such a prankster. 

But I will tell you something positive now: I love pen-pals, and Alex is my hero. Thank You!

Im feeling a little under the weather, over the river, and through the woods.
its cool though, dont sweat it. I have this rad burn um its a blister. i like its story so im looking into writing a sequel. yeeeeeeah. tonight was a knight, a k-nig-it(if you get it then i like you). its the cutest when they say so um wanna hang out some time, duh you little cute face@@! so ya know it was like me amn shniggles took a drive to the JIB-IZZLE and he was all damn jim, i dont get a discount! i work at sears! jim was all shit i dont know a hjim but i can call jack for you. curly fries galore.galore.galore. ill tell you a story now. reeeeeady okay: so one day sears was walking along, walking along and all of a sudden he was like slavery is SO in style these days!!@ and he was overwhelmed galore! so he came up to lindsay and was all hey lindsay hows it going? oh its going good ya know. oh yeah thats cool, say lindsay you wanna be in style!? and lindsay was all hell yeah sears! so sears all thats saweeet! and then the next day lindsay discovers to her horror that oh no, whats this!? she works seven days in a row! and it accumulates to over 60 hours~!!!>>! oh my lindsay! dont even try to be in style! then she realizesshe must also attend school and take finals and probably go christmas shopping sometime soon! whoa dang. so as she wallows in her self pity, sears is off in some foreign land barricaded deep inside a dark cave with osama bin laden and an echoing satanic laugh can be heard from inside its dark interior.

and fade to black....

I went to New York and you should be jealous. Pretty tree Singing trees Kelsey knows how to razzle dazzle 'em (so does that guy in the corner) Gotta grab the bull by the balls I met Hugh Grant We're in love Us and Simon hate you Jimi and Salvador look pretty awesome Hahaha...mmm I don't know I love nakeds in time square Dear New York, I miss you I'll see you soon.

You know what that is don't you?
Certainly, you're well acquainted.
That noise, that jump, that bump rising; 
surfacing, breaching, coming for air.
That's your heart setting down past the horizon.
It's the sun pulsating. It's beating.
It's beating down on your brow and the brow bows down.
You know what that means don't you?
Of course, you've felt it before.
That pressure, that pain, that rush of ecstasy seeping through your veins.
That's a lung collapsing down past your knees.
That's a tower crumbling back to the seas.
That's sticks and stones springing every which way.
Every stick for his self, every stone for hers.
You know you can't stop it dont you?
Obviously, since you've failed before.
That cycle, that track, that Sisyphean task.
It's inhaling the poison and reeping the benefits.
It's exhaling the smoke and expelling epidemic.
Breathe in, breathe out. Die, kill.
Murder, suicide. Genocide, pesticide, ostracize, pasteurize.
Setting and beating. Collapsing and crumbling.

You know what this is don't you?
I'm sure. We were well acquainted.
You may say I'm a dreamer But I'm not the only one...

If I was a smarter girl I would know when enough was enough
Was enough too much?
It's tough.
Does it ever stop, 
rewind
fastforward
pause.

I want to pause.

I'd like to know when something has reached its capacity
When change or growth are no longer options
I think we all would
So we can give up.
and quietly take our
leave,
excuse ourselves from  
guilt

---
Nothing means much of anything anymore.

Don't look back
Dylan said it
and before that
satchel paige 
said it and 
said why

but neither
specified when

let me start
the list

1. after smoking
a joint
on the freeway.


            I found that pinned up over my dad's desk. Makes me smile.



I'm going to New York, so I'll see you suckers later.

Today I watched My Big Fat Greek Wedding. It's a fun movie. It was the first movie I ever watched at Madstone Theatre. I miss that place a lot. I hate when places like that close up. Because it makes me think, when will I ever see that man with the awesome moustache again? Probably never. 
Also, if it would have stayed open me and my mama wouldn't have had to drive all the way to Camelview to see Sideways. I'm glad we did though. On our way we passed My Big Fat Greek Restaurant and I thought that was funny. It was a good movie. It was crowded and I'm pretty sure I was the youngest person in attendance. That's okay.

It was nice out tonight.




I love Arizona Novembers.

Where ever your travels may take you, lets make a pact right now that November will be our month. Lets promise that where ever we may be we'll come back here in November. All the Novembers to come will be ours. Just ours. Promise me that, okay? Just think, this time next year we'll find each other again and no matter how much distance has grown between us we will know that by November we will have found each other again and we can never truly be lost.

Well, I guess perhaps this is an update-worthy occurrence. So today I recieved a letter from ASU. Turns out that I am the recipient of an ASU Provost Scholarship, or something like that. Anyway, that means $5500 a year renewable each year. $22000! Yay for me. I think. My mom was definitely a thousand times more excited than I was. I said to her what if I didn't even want to go to ASU and she literally crumpled to the ground saying "Don't do this to me!" She has a flare for the dramatic.I didn't really want to stay here. I wanted to go somewhere new. But alas, I now have 22000 more reasons to stay. I'm kidding right? Oh of course I am. This is great news. 

I'm dumb. This should be my real post...

YAYAY OOMGGG I WIN YESS FREE MONEYE UAAHGHHHH SOO AWESOMEEMM  WWWEEEEEEEEEE!@#((*!!!

Some things I find funny are how I show up to work an hour and a half late and no one minds (okay really they just didn't notice). how my dad makes me listen to Lyle Lovett a lot and I like it. how all my exes live in Texas. how I can never bring myself to do math homework...ever. how my english teacher thinks I have OCD. how I have
how I am extremely susceptible to hiccups. how I got my Sears associate discount card in the mail! Now I'm going to buy a dishwasher. how sometimes I pretend that I'm on the show Motormouth and I sing really loudly in my car to make sure I win...just in case! how whenever I put on a pair of pants it's guaranteed that I will find a movie ticket in the back pocket. Today was I <3Huckabee's and Friday Night Lights. how I like to make lists. how Ms. Frahm makes awesome faces. how I like to think that Denny's is our Peach Pit. how I think I'm getting sick. and how I really love this song...

I enjoy when my father and I discuss politics and watch Larry King Live. It's a good time. I think he's a pretty smart guy and it's interesting to hear his perspectives and have him explain the paradox that is our government. I don't usually like talking about politics and such, especially with people at school, mainly because that's all it is: just people talking in order to hear their own voice and no one is really listening. And I'm not one to parade my opinion in an audacious fashion, thinking that it's actually persuading people. So anyway, we talked about everything from Ross Perot to the electoral college to the Drudge Report to Prop. 400 to Reaganomics directly putting bee-keepers out of business. Yeah, that's what I call a good time. I only blame him for being born 6 months too late. 

Anyway, I really just needed an update because I got sick of looking at previous entries.

Today I got in the shower with my glasses on. I had shampoo on my head before I realized something was wrong, or maybe that nothing was right. Who can tell anymore anyhow? Anyway. This is jumbled and confused. A word jumble, a Sunday paper activity, a jumbled jungle, a Jungle Jim's. Crazy jumping from this to that from that to this, back and forth, to and fro, here or there. Exactly. It's like rain on your wedding day. Ironic? Alanis thinks so. So do I. Two peas in a pod. This is just an excercise. Like tae-bo. Like a thigh-master. Like spam and cannibalism. Yes, exactly like that. An amazing wonderment. A wondering amazingment. Too true, too true indeed. Cellar door. Cell-ar Do-or. Beauty in the form of sound, syllables, pro-nun-ciation. Sound it out. Ssssssounnnndd iiittt ouuut. You'll see. You will. I promise. A promise. A co-promise. Compromise? We'll see. We will. I mean who can actually see for miles and miles anyway? The who thats who any way. I haven't seen you in miles and miles. About 10,000 of them are between me and everything else. Distance. Don't touch that! There's reason behind the distance. There's distance behind each reasoning. Don't look back in anger...A meaningful mantra, right? Write. Don't be mad at the kilometers. They're just killing the meters, the oh meters. Like killing time between here and there, to and fro, once and again. See. It all relates. It's all relative. Some relatives just love to get drunk. Some relatives get drunk to love. It's the same, right? Write. Who can tell anymore anyhow? Anyway.

"Life is like the surf, so give yourself away like the sea."

Don't hold back. Embrace each new everything.

Sweet Jesus my life is depressing.

Some people do not grow from past experiences. They decide to rot in the same stagnant surroundings forever and always. They choose to decay; a wasted life.
Decaying in a house he cannot even call his own, getting high with two 15 year old boys: what a proud day in his life this must be.

This house; I swear, it's depressing.


So I left and
3 CDs
9 books
2 DVDs &
$100 later

I still feel the same.
This house still feels the same.

Tonight I was sifting through some old journals that I have had since freshman year. I like looking back from time to time, it's more comforting than looking forward. And it's funny to think that what I wrote four years ago is what I am going through once again. Nothing changes, time just passes and things stay the same. Anyway, I found this excerpt to be amusing:

"Sometimes I hurt so bad on the inside that I want to puke for days so that everything tainted inside of me will be expelled from my body. That's how I want to start fresh. I should probably just develop an eating disorder."

I'm funny.

Who knew Sunday's could be fun?
50 years and counting.
Too much wine.
Bare asses.
pass out.
andersen jr high.
Rain.
Dead batteries.
Rain.
Threw a telescope in a tree.
Crazy drivers.
end.

Today was definitely a kick ya in the crotch, spit on your neck, wretched type of day.

Why won't this day just end?
It's only seven, but I'm going to bed now.

I can't sleep.
I'm too stressed to sleep.
I'm stressed because I lack super powers.
I wish I could buy some on ebay.
I'd purchase the 'Be Able To Be In 2 Places At Once' super power for only $11.99.
And with that purchase I would receive a 5 dollar sanity rebate and 8 hours of sleep with no down payments.
Then I would be happy and to show my eternal gratitude, I'd give my first born child to ebay, just to say thanks.

Relationships don't work they way they do on television and in the movies. Will they? Won't they? And then they finally do, and they're happy forever. Give me a break. Nine out of ten of them end because they weren't right for each other to begin with, and half of the ones who get married get divorced anyway, and I'm telling you right now, through all this stuff I have not become a cynic. I haven't. Yes, I do happen to believe that love is mainly about pushing chocolate covered candies and, you know, in some cultures, a chicken. You can call me a sucker, I don't care, because I do believe in it. Bottom line: couples who are truly right for each other wade through the same crap as everybody else, but the big difference is they don't let it take them down. One of those two people will stand up and fight for that relationship every time. If it's right, and they're real lucky, one of them will say something, always.

Today was a work day. I worked from 1030 till 5 at Sears then I'm home for approximately 15 minutes when a fellow coworker from the pool begs me to work for her from 530 to 900. I do it because I am a saint! She owes me too because it was shitty and I mean that in the literal sense of the word. Nothing changes at the pool. I love it. I also love when the little kids scream random things when they jump off the high dive. It amuses me to no end. Tonight I heard everything from "CHEESE WITH HAIR" to my personal favorite "IM A JESUS FREAK". Oh kids, they say the darndest things. It's strange but things like that really make my night. 

I'll tell you what else makes my night, hanging out with the swim team (aka mormons) and playing games where we hit each other with newspapers. Awesome. I'm trying to keep myself busy and do things that make me happy. 

It's a tricky business; being happy.

uggggggggggghhhhhhh....my head is about to explode, I can feel it. Going to school sick amplifies every irritation about a thousand times. So its safe to say I wanted to kill myself by the end of the day, actually I just wanted to kill everyone else. I'm murderer.
So I have successfully completed the first day of my last year in high school.

Wow I love storms. I'm glad it stormed like crazy this evening, oh yeah and good thing I was definitely at work because I would never want to miss out all that madness. I will tell you a little story about it....

It was during a pool party and we had just finished telling everyone that they needed to evacuate the pool because there was lightning and whatnot. About thirty seconds later it starts pouring. Nice. Everyone gathers into our little guard room. About 50 people and the majority was under the age of twelve. Us awesome lifeguards run out in the rain/lightning/thunder/madness and save all their food and bring it inside. And you thought we just saved people. Then we all gather under a small overhang outside our guard room and watch as the lightning begins to surround us. CRACK! Ohh look there goes one of our lights. CRACK! Oh look it just struck our baby pool. Awesome. Except for I screamed everytime and grabbed onto the person nearest me. Then it was over. The people finally left. We cleaned a little. Realized it was pointless. Found some dead baby birds that got blown out of their nest. I cried. We played on the diving boards. And our pool is trashed. The end. 


I'm not happy, and I have a headache.

Today I went and took my senior picture. I really hate posing for pictures, especially when the photographer is some weirdo creep guy like the one I had today. He would make awkward comments to me after each picture he took like, "Oh wow, your parents make good kids," and "Oh yeah, that right there is why boys go off and fight wars for our country." Riiiight, how about you just stop talking.

This evening my father and I went out on a little date. He wanted to buy me clothes and take me out to dinner. So he did and we did. It was sweet. He told me he had a reality check recently and he realized that he doesn't spend enough time with us. It's nice that he's trying now. 

Anyway, school is starting in less than a week and you can bet that I am totally looking forward to seeing everyone's smiling face on a daily basis. 

Goodnight.

I have worked a total of 21 hours over
the past two days.

I have slept a total of 9 hours over 
the past two nights.

that ratio is no good. 

today...

i finished my book at work.
i found a dollar on the ground.
is my cousins' 18th birthday.
i had to say goodbye again.



i'm tired.

this is a convo i had with my father this evening:

me: dad are you a metrosexual?
dad: yeah, i ride the subways all the time!
me: ....what?
dad: yeah you know the subways in a metropolitan.
me: uh.

hilarious.


i had lovely conversations tonight.
some people make me really happy.

i work 40 hours this week.
that means 40 hours of sitting in the scorching sun.
and sweating. a lot.
i hate it when the little kids climb the high dive and discover that they are too scared to take the plunge. 
i yell at them to jump off so i don't have to go help them down.


i hate making small talk with people.
it's kind of annoying.

i hope kelsey got arrested.

I fucking hate jet-lag.

I just slept for 11 hours, now what the hell am I supposed to do?

I'm back.

I've been up since 12:30am AZ time.
I tried laying down, but the sleep thing just wasn't happening. 

Some advice; never go to a pay phone to make a phone call by yourself in the middle of the night when in the streets of Rome (although I'm sure this advice applies everywhere) because someone will try to kidnap you or something equally as scary. Keep that in mind. I will. 

Europe was amazing, a once-in-a-lifetime type of experience to say the least.
It was everything and nothing I expected all at the same time.
I won't go too into detail because I'm pretty sure describing it here would hardly do it the justice it truly deserves. 
I'll just say that it was wonderful, inspiring, beautiful, and most importantly something different from anything I have ever known or experienced.
